The paper deals with the problem of joint 3D positioning and network synchronization in 5G networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves signal processing and estimation techniques, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses a channel model and evaluates the performance of the proposed methods using trajectories of vehicles and unmanned aerial vehicles, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO).
